  "title": "Finance Executive",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Well Established Company</strong></li><li><strong>Basic $3000 - $3500 + AWS + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li><strong>Excellent Welfare and Benefits + Career progression</strong></li><li><strong>Working location: East </strong></li><li><strong>Working day: Monday to Friday</strong></li><li><strong>Working hours: 8.00am to 5.30pm </strong></li></ul><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Handle day-to-day accounts receivable and payable duties using AutoCount, including invoicing, payment processing, and follow-ups</strong></li><li>Ensure accurate and timely recording of all financial transactions in the accounting system</li><li><strong>Manage petty cash reimbursements and conduct monthly bank reconciliations</strong></li><li>Support inventory management, including stock movements and participation in half-yearly and annual stock counts</li><li><strong>Assist in month-end closing, GST submissions, and audit preparation</strong></li><li>Ensure compliance with internal control procedures and good corporate governance practices</li><li>Other ad hoc duties as assigned</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Possess minimum Diploma in Accountancy, LCCI, CAT, or equivalent</li><li><strong>Minimum 1 year of relevant accounting experience, preferably in a manufacturing environment</strong></li><li>Proficient in AutoCount accounting system and Microsoft Office</li></ul><p>Candidates are encouraged to apply this position via <strong>Apply Now </strong>button with the following information in the resume</p><ul><li>Work experiences and job responsibilities</li><li>Current and Expected salary</li><li>Reason for leaving</li><li>Date of availability</li><li>Education background</li></ul><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</p><p>LIONG ZHAO GUAN (R22107632)</p><p>EA Recruitment Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 21C0492</p>",
